main event: Several witnesses observed a disc-shaped object hovering over a wooded area near North Forrestville, Maryland on October 6, 1968.
interesting points: The object was described as approximately 30 feet in diameter, with a bright reddish-orange glow emanating from its surface.
The object made no sound and hovered silently for several minutes before accelerating rapidly and disappearing from sight.

Photographic evidence was obtained, showing the bright disc-shaped object against the night sky. Analysis of the photographic data indicates that the object was a physical, metallic craft and not a misidentification of a conventional phenomenon.

Several other residents in the immediate vicinity also reported seeing the same object at approximately the same time, and their accounts were generally consistent with the primary witness's description.
While the exact nature and origin of the object remain unknown, this case is being classified as an unresolved unidentified flying object under Project Blue Book.
sighted object: disc-shaped object with a bright reddish-orange glow
